Chugoku Electric Power Co. will build
a 3-megawatt solar plant in Yamaguchi prefecture, western  Japan .  The utility aims to begin operations at the plant in the
fiscal year beginning April 2014, according to a statement on
its website today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
